,"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":298,"output":16,"totalTokens":148993,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":148679,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776175013389,"responseId":"062d7aa722768603ee68eed99796f84c","__openclaw":{"id":"67c2127e","seq":1297}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 14:05 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 3\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV): running — 5-min progress monitoring (QLHV ecosystem) — ~54m\n• cron:6f3323ef (5p DTLX): running — 5-min progress monitoring (DTLX ecosystem) — ~6h 39m\n• cron:e7885813 (this run): running — Agent Status to Lead (every 10m) — just started\n\nPipeline: **HEARTBEAT_OK** ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• ⚠️ 2 zombie sessions lingering (pre-existing, no new failures)\n• No blockers.\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}],"timestamp":1776175607224,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","sourceTool":"sessions_send"},"__openclaw":{"id":"4b564df5","seq":1298}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Heartbeat OK. Silent."},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":296,"output":15,"totalTokens":149248,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":148937,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776175607413,"responseId":"062d7cf9f8d9584acc03aecf5e3d4d39","__openclaw":{"id":"a09f3602","seq":1299}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","label":"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776175612637,"sessionId":"569f7a27-3677-48e3-b3db-ec35e7aa3b90","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":45601,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776152701090,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/569f7a27-3677-48e3-b3db-ec35e7aa3b90.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the heartbeat-state.json baseline. Let me compare the current sessions list against it.\n\n**Baseline (heartbeat-state.json, last updated 13:36 UTC):**\n\nSessions:\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` → status: running\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` → status: running\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` → status: running\n\n\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` → status: done\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492` → status: done\n6. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` → status: done\n7. `agent:master-orchestrator:main` → status: done\n8. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:b653a6c0-143b-4b53-a242-034bc5fd9fca` → status: running (stale zombie)\n9. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ac986a8d-2425-40c7-835b-ed9b101b0bff` → status: running (stale zombie)\n\nNow looking at the current session state. The cron jobs are still running as expected, though the first one appears to have shifted to a different execution context in the current timestamp.\n\nComparing to the baseline, the key change I'm seeing is the telegram:direct:6053576134 session has moved to done status with an endedAt timestamp of around 13:15 UTC, which represents a state change from the baseline.\n\nThe stale cron sessions remain unchanged as expected. The QLHV group telegram session also stayed done throughout the cycle. Overall, this looks like normal session lifecycle transitions with no new failures or blockers emerging. Since the system is stable and the only state change is that session completion, I should report this as a minimal update to the group.\n\nLooking back at the earlier reports though, I notice the Lead direct session shows endedAt 13:15 UTC but the 14:05 UTC report indicated it was still active and receiving messages—there's a discrepancy in the timestamps I need to reconcile.\n\nChecking the actual session data more carefully: the direct session ended at 13:15 UTC (timestamp 1776162158012), which is after the heartbeat state's lastSeen of 13:36 UTC. The session's last message was a 13:00 UTC heartbeat that timed out waiting for a response, even though the session had already been marked as done in the heartbeat state. So it appears the heartbeat state is tracking the session as done, which aligns with the current status.\n\nLooking at the session history, the Lead direct session actually shows two heartbeats at 13:56 and 14:01 UTC in the messages, but the session status is marked as \"done\"—suggesting these messages were delivered as inter-session notifications rather than through a running session. Comparing the current 14:06 UTC state against the baseline from 13:36 UTC, the direct session was already marked done in the baseline, so this isn't a new change.\n\nSince the heartbeat state at 13:36 already had the session as done, and the current sessions list shows the same done status, there's no state change to report—the cron job at 13:56 appears to have used a different delivery mechanism rather than spawning a new running session. Based on the sessions list timestamp comparison, the lead direct session appears to be done in both the current and baseline snapshots, so there's no state change to report—I'll stay silent and exit."},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current sessions against `heartbeat-state.json` baseline (13:36 UTC):\n\n**Baseline state:**\n- 3 cron sessions: running ✅\n- Lead direct: done ✅\n- QLHV group: done ✅\n- DTLX group: done ✅\n- 2 stale zombies: running (pre-existing)\n\n**Current state (14:06 UTC):** All identical — same 3 cron sessions running, same done sessions, same zombies. No new failures, no blockers, no new sessions.\n\n**No changes detected. Silent exit.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1774,"output":933,"totalTokens":46534,"cacheRead":14264,"cacheWrite":29563,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776175669506,"responseId":"062d7d36e7cbfdfd81d649029bc393db","__openclaw":{"id":"1ecdade4","seq":8}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","kind":"other","channel":"unknown","label":"Cron: Agent Status to Lead","displayName":"Cron: Agent Status to Lead","updatedAt":1776175501323,"sessionId":"5f194a43-4dd8-4854-9a32-c4742405b653","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":35313,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776174329576,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/5f194a43-4dd8-4854-9a32-c4742405b653.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full sessions list. Let me analyze the active master-orchestrator sessions (excluding this cron session):\n\n1. **This cron session**: `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` - running - Agent Status to Lead (this session itself)\n\n2. **cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7** - running - \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\" (QLHV ecosystem) - startedAt: 1776172286015 → running for ~54 minutes (from 13:51 to 14:05 UTC)\n   \n3. **cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31** - running - \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\" (DTLX ecosystem) - startedAt: 1776152701090 → running for ~6h 39m (started around 07:25 UTC)\n\n4. **telegram:direct:6053576134** - done - Lead direct session (received the 13:55 UTC report)\n\n5. **telegram:group:-5163901258** - still active in the Telegram group session\n\n6. **cron:b653a6c0-143b-4b53-a242-034bc5fd9fca** - still running but looks like an orphaned cron job with no activity, likely a zombie that needs cleanup\n\n7. **cron:ac986a8d-2425-40c7-835b-ed9b101b0bff** - another zombie session, same issue with no messages\n\nThe rest are either completed or failed subagents and child sessions that aren't relevant here. So filtering down, I've got this cron session plus three others still actively running. Looking at the execution times for these sessions. The first one ran for about 54 minutes, the second for roughly 6 hours and 39 minutes, and this current session is just starting up. Now I need to figure out how to format this for the report to send to Lead."},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll compile the report and send it to Lead.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ks7ppo3jkea7_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 14:05 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 3\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV): running — 5-min progress monitoring (QLHV ecosystem) — ~54m\n• cron:6f3323ef (5p DTLX): running — 5-min progress monitoring (DTLX ecosystem) — ~6h 39m\n• cron:e7885813 (this run): running — Agent Status to Lead (every 10m) — just started\n\nPipeline: **HEARTBEAT_OK** ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• ⚠️ 2 zombie sessions lingering (pre-existing, no new failures)\n• No blockers.\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":20377,"output":702,"totalTokens":35234,"cacheRead":13849,"cacheWrite":306,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776175525529,"responseId":"062d7ca612a40669343410d5aabfa4c5","__openclaw":{"id":"a9961b64","seq":4}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sessions_send timed out. But this is likely because the session was \"done\" - it had ended with \"status\": \"done\" in the sessions list. The send likely went through but the wait for response timed out. This is fine - the message should have been delivered. Let me check the result more carefully.\n\nActually, looking at the session key `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134`, it was \"status\": \"done\" in the sessions list. But it had a delivery context configured for Telegram, so sessions_send should work. The timeout means the target session didn't respond within the timeout window, but the message was likely delivered.\n\n\nI'll exit with NO_REPLY since the delivery probably succeeded despite the timeout."},{"type":"text","text":"NO_REPLY"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":184,"output":160,"totalTokens":35473,"cacheRead":14084,"cacheWrite":21045,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776175573652,"responseId":"062d7cd7762a863945f99f15d937efb0","__openclaw":{"id":"4e53e775","seq":6}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:main","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat","to":"heartbeat"},"updatedAt":1776174335279,"sessionId":"bca9bbb9-d1eb-408d-9e3d-14dd521dcc45","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":71196,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1776174316801,"endedAt":1776174329766,"runtimeMs":12965,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","lastTo":"heartbeat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/bca9bbb9-d1eb-408d-9e3d-14dd521dcc45.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Quick check of sessions."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x3zz9h2uieky_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":5,"activeMinutes":10,"messageLimit":0}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1605,"output":54,"totalTokens":69493,"c